    "body": "I am stuck. Going to work on something else and probably switch to thinking about any good solution later.\r\n\r\nThe problem is I see no way to guarantee security. The only thing we can do after account recovery is to announce that we need contacts. But after that everybody can say \"Hey, I am your contact\" and there is no way to guarantee that it is true. So it means that almost everybody can be added to your contact list after recovery.\r\nThe solution that seems to be obvious in this situation is to use some verification string that was generated before (and, of course, both users should know this string). But the recovered contact has nothing except its address and public key, so we cannot generate the same string one more time without any additional information. Once again, the private sharing of any information between to contacts doesn't seem possible in the case when we have no information about the contact.\r\n\r\nThe code for sharing unencrypted information is in `feature/#240` branch, but I don't think it is a good idea to use this code now.",
